===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|[[advertising]]}} A [[catch phrase]] associated with the [[product]] or [[service]] being advertised.
# A [[distinctive]] [[phrase]] of a [[person]] or [[group]] of [[people]].
#* {{RQ:Wodehouse Offing|chapter=XVIII|passage=[Bertie Wooster:] “Right-ho,” I said, not much liking the assignment, but liking less the idea of endeavouring to thwart this incandescent aunt in her current frame of mind. Safety first, is the Wooster '''slogan'''.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[battle cry]] among the ancient [[highlander]]s of [[Scotland]].
#* '''1805''', Walter Scott, "The Lay of the Last Minstrel", IV. xxvii:
#*: To heaven the Border slogan rung, / The English war-cry answer'd wide.

